claim: The Eiffel Tower is in Paris, France.
reference: Paris is home to the Eiffel Tower, a wrought-iron lattice tower on the Champ de Mars.
label: supported

claim: The Great Wall of China can be seen from the Moon with the naked eye.
reference: No man-made structure is visible from the Moon with the naked eye; the Great Wall is not visible from that distance.
label: refuted

claim: Water boils at 100°C at sea level.
reference: At standard atmospheric pressure (1 atm), the boiling point of water is 100 degrees Celsius.
label: supported

claim: Venus is the closest planet to the Sun.
reference: Mercury is the closest planet to the Sun; Venus is the second.
label: refuted

reference: Python is a high-level, general-purpose programming language created by Guido van Rossum.
label: supported

claim: Mount Everest is over 9000 meters tall.
reference: Mount Everest's height is approximately 8848.86 meters above sea level, which is below 9000 meters.
label: refuted

claim: Photosynthesis converts carbon dioxide and water into glucose and oxygen.
reference: During photosynthesis, plants convert CO2 and H2O into glucose (C6H12O6) and O2 using light energy.
label: supported

claim: The human body has exactly 300 bones.
reference: Adults have 206 bones; newborns have around 270 which fuse during growth.
label: refuted

claim: The speed of light in vacuum is approximately 3×10^8 m/s.
reference: In vacuum, light travels at about 299,792,458 meters per second, commonly approximated as 3×10^8 m/s.
label: supported

reference: The capital of Australia is Canberra, not Sydney.
label: refuted
